node.text:
The best time off is whenever I get to be in a beautiful, natural outdoor setting, getting my butt up a mountain, up a river, down a mountain or otherwise in motion- even if it’s just down the greenway or the beach. Sunshine is good, but cannot be planned. Good company always makes it better...
So I was looking forward to this trip to #acadianationalpark with @evanlaettner for a while now! 

For these kinds of activities, clothing is important. Comfort, breathability, flexibility, and wind and water resistance are key. 

A partnership with @revolutionrace was an easy fit (no pun intended). Their pants were the best for any hike we tackled- so much stretch! (I’m looking forward to wearing these for chainsaw days) And I love how the windproof shell is so quiet- none of that “swoosh swoosh!!” 

If you like to get outdoors, check their stuff out- follow the link in my stories. Use code 15WOODTURN for 15% off. I’ve also got a link in my bio. They’re available on Amazon too- for all you instant gratification junkies. 

Featured:
Norwand Pants
Silence Proshell Jacket

#ad #natureisourplayground #adventure #optoutside #goodcompany #hikersofinstagram #naturalwonderland #proudlysponsored

node.text:
The landscapes of Acadia provide a pretty amazing backdrop for exploring a little photography...

but really, for a lot of things. For a little relaxation, fresh air, visiting with my parents (and their Mainecoon), hiking, eating lots of lobster, and just plain taking a few days off. Like all the best things in life, it’s never long enough. 

1. Jordan Pond
2. From Gorham Mountain
3. From Northeast Harbor
4. Thuya boat landing with Captain Marcus, a.k.a. Dad
5. Otter Cliffs
6. Bernard, ME
7. My parents in Bernard
8. Hangin with Murphy- tryin to get some love
9. With my mother
10. From Pemetic Mountain trail

People photos by @evanlaettner
Selfies and Landscape pics by yours truly

#maine #mainecoon #acadianationalpark 
#landscapephotography #family

node.text:
Turner update:
She is fully recovered from her surgery three weeks ago to remove a cancerous tumor from her jaw. Back to running in the yard, chilling in the studio, chasing cats, and being her sweet self! We’re hoping that it doesn’t come back and enjoying all the moments we have together. She does seem a bit more affectionate in recent days. And she now has this badass snaggle tooth look. Thank you so much for all the well wishes and positive vibes ❤️ 

#mygirl #twoturners #happytogether #dogsofinsta #oldgirl #snaggletooth
